{"key":"processedPost-7534767","value":{"id":7534767,"first":7534684,"last":7534834,"when":1192810976,"utime":"10/19/07 07:22 PM","content":"Hepa filters are cheap. I've seen them for $20 and for the most part, they're worthless.  What you want for successful mycology is a <i>laminar flow</i> hepa filter.  Without laminar flow, you're just swirling the air around, which will pick up contaminants and blow them into your work.  By working in front of a laminar air stream, the air, thus contaminants, leave the area of your work, flowing back towards you and away from the sterile media.<br />RR","title":"Re: Is a 50 buck HEPA filterer worth it?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}